.SH NAME
Tcl_CreateCloseHandlez, Tcl_DeleteCloseHandlez \- arrange fo' callbacks when channels is closed
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
\fB#include <tcl.h>\fR
.sp
void
\fBTcl_CreateCloseHandlez\fR(\fIchannel, proc, clientData\fR)
.sp
void
\fBTcl_DeleteCloseHandlez\fR(\fIchannel, proc, clientData\fR)
.sp
.SH ARGUMENTS
.AS Tcl_CloseProc clientData
.AP Tcl_Channel channel in
Da channel fo' which ta create or delete a cold-ass lil close callback.
.AP Tcl_CloseProc *proc in
Da procedure ta booty-call as tha callback.
.AP ClientData clientData in
Arbitrary one-word value ta pass ta \fIproc\fR.
.BE

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\fBTcl_CreateCloseHandlez\fR arranges fo' \fIproc\fR ta be called when
\fIchannel\fR is closed wit \fBTcl_Close\fR or
\fBTcl_UnregisterChannel\fR, or rockin tha Tcl \fBclose\fR command.
\fIProc\fR should match tha followin prototype:
.PP
.CS
typedef void Tcl_CloseProc(
        ClientData \fIclientData\fR);
.CE
.PP
Da \fIclientData\fR is tha same ol' dirty as tha value provided up in tha call to
\fBTcl_CreateCloseHandlez\fR.
.PP
\fBTcl_DeleteCloseHandlez\fR removes a cold-ass lil close callback fo' \fIchannel\fR.
Da \fIproc\fR n' \fIclientData\fR identify which close callback to
remove; \fBTcl_DeleteCloseHandlez\fR do not a god damn thang if its \fIproc\fR and
\fIclientData\fR arguments do not match tha \fIproc\fR n' \fIclientData\fR
for a  close handlez fo' \fIchannel\fR.

